-ioctl

http://manpagesfr.free.fr/man/man2/ioctl.2.html

◦ execve
	execve("/bin/ls", av, NULL);
		-> NULL represente l'environnement
 -> appel systeme FORK (man fork)

"pid_t 		father;"

father = fork();
if (father > 0)
{
	wait();
	PRINTF("I M YOUR FATHER");
}
if (father == 0)
{
	sleep(3);
	execve("/bin/ls", av, NULL);
}

◦ malloc,free

◦ access

-> permet de checker les permissions 
		access(path, R_OK)	read permission
		access(path, W_OK) write permission
		access(path, X_OK) execute/search
		access(path, F_OK) existence test

◦ open, close, read, write
◦ opendir, readdir, closedir

◦ getcwd, chdir
 	//get working directory pathanme
 	getcwd(buf, NULL);
 	chdir(path) -> wd = path now;

◦ stat, lstat, fstat
	stat/lstat -> obtient l'information sur un ficher
	fstat -> obient l'information a partir d'un file descriptor;

◦ fork, execve
	cree un nouveau process: - uniqueID
							 - different parent ID
							 - copy of parents
							 (see setrlimit)
	       process ID           see getpid(2)
           parent process ID    see getppid(2)
           process group ID     see getpgrp(2)
           access groups        see getgroups(2)
           working directory    see chdir(2)
           root directory       see chroot(2)
           control terminal     see termios(4)
           resource usages      see getrusage(2)
           interval timers      see getitimer(2)
           resource limits      see getrlimit(2)
           file mode mask       see umask(2)
           signal mask          see sigaction(2), sigsetmask(2)

◦ wait, waitpid, wait3, wait4
	no entiendo señor;
◦ signal, kill
	-> pour les processus qui merde
	sigaction (2)
◦ exit

